      <title>丹麦总理展开旋风之旅以争取对格陵兰的支持</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-28/danish-premier-starts-whirlwind-tour-for-support-over-greenland</link>
      <description><![CDATA[就在丹麦拨出资金用于保卫北极岛屿之际，丹麦首相梅特·弗雷德里克森开始访问欧洲主要国家首都，以争取对格陵兰岛争端的支持。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-28/danish-premier-starts-whirlwind-tour-for-support-over-greenland</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 28 Jan 2025 07:00:08 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>五角大楼以进展为由向洛克希德·马丁公司免除更多 F-35 升级费用</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-28/pentagon-frees-more-payments-to-lockheed-on-f-35-upgrades-citing-progress</link>
      <description><![CDATA[五角大楼将洛克希德马丁公司为 F-35 战机预留的资金每架减少 120 万美元，因为承包商正在验证和安装该战斗机最强大的硬件和软件的最新版本。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-28/pentagon-frees-more-payments-to-lockheed-on-f-35-upgrades-citing-progress</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 28 Jan 2025 05:30:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>邦迪海滩议员称气候行动不能等待经济好转</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-28/bondi-beach-mp-says-climate-action-can-t-wait-for-better-economy</link>
      <description><![CDATA[澳大利亚独立议员阿莱格拉·斯宾德（Allegra Spender）坚称，气候行动不能因国家经济困难而推迟，并为下次选举后出现少数派政府的情况提出了潜在诉求。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-28/bondi-beach-mp-says-climate-action-can-t-wait-for-better-economy</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 28 Jan 2025 04:14:11 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>特朗普称印度总理莫迪将于 2 月访问白宫</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-28/trump-says-india-s-modi-likely-to-visit-white-house-in-february</link>
      <description><![CDATA[唐纳德·特朗普表示，纳伦德拉·莫迪可能将于二月访问白宫，这将使印度总理成为美国总统就职以来首批访问华盛顿的外国领导人之一。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-28/trump-says-india-s-modi-likely-to-visit-white-house-in-february</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 28 Jan 2025 02:27:58 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>日本反对党将在未达成更大税收协议的情况下阻止预算</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-28/japan-opposition-party-to-block-budget-if-ishiba-stands-ground-on-tax-ceiling</link>
      <description><![CDATA[日本首相石破茂政府的政策负责人表示，如果石破政府不向寻求更大免税额度的小反对党做出更多让步，其年度预算将面临被否决的风险。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-28/japan-opposition-party-to-block-budget-if-ishiba-stands-ground-on-tax-ceiling</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 28 Jan 2025 01:25:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>特朗普誓言对关键领域征收远超 2.5% 的关税</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-27/trump-vows-near-future-tariffs-calls-deepseek-progress-good</link>
      <description><![CDATA[美国总统唐纳德·特朗普表示，他希望实施“远高于” 2.5% 的全面关税，这是周一发出的一系列信号中的最新一个，表明他正准备实施大规模征税，以重塑美国供应链。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-27/trump-vows-near-future-tariffs-calls-deepseek-progress-good</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Jan 2025 23:43:27 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>特朗普告诉众议院共和党人他希望获得资金来完成修建隔离墙</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-27/trump-tells-house-republicans-he-wants-wall-immigration-funds</link>
      <description><![CDATA[总统唐纳德·特朗普告诉众议院共和党人，他希望他们能够通过立法，为修建边境墙提供资金，并加强驱逐出境力度，这是他雄心勃勃的议程的一部分，该议程还包括延长他签署的减税措施和促进更多的石油和天然气生产。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-27/trump-tells-house-republicans-he-wants-wall-immigration-funds</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Jan 2025 23:28:17 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>贝森特获参议院批准出任美国财政部长</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-27/trump-s-treasury-secretary-pick-scott-bessent-wins-senate-confirmation</link>
      <description><![CDATA[美国参议院批准斯科特·贝森特为下一任财政部长，他将成为唐纳德·特朗普总统及其减税、放松管制和贸易再平衡等广泛议程的首席经济发言人。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-01-27/trump-s-treasury-secretary-pick-scott-bessent-wins-senate-confirmation</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Jan 2025 23:10:32 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
